Interview Questions
1.	What is your current process for managing late or missing work on Canvas?
2.	How often do students submit work after it has been marked missing?
3.	What steps do you currently take to update a submission status?
4.	Which part of the process takes the longest?
5.	Which part of the process is the most frustrating?
6.	How often do incorrect submission statuses occur?
7.	What impact do incorrect statuses have on your workflow?
8.	How do students usually respond when their work is incorrectly marked missing?
9.	What information do you need to see immediately when checking submissions?
10.	How do you currently keep track of overdue tasks?
11.	Do you use any reminders or notes to help manage missing work?
12.	Would automated reminders improve your workflow? Why or why not?
13.	What type of reminder system would work best for you?
14.	How often would you want reminders to appear?
15.	What features in Canvas currently work well for managing submissions?
16.	What features in Canvas do you think are missing?
17.	How important is being able to filter by class?
18.	How important is being able to filter by individual student?
19.	Would colour coding or visual indicators help you identify missing work faster?
20.	What devices do you mainly use when marking or updating submissions?
21.	Are there any technical limitations on school computers that should be considered?
22.	Would you prefer the application to work online, offline, or both?
23.	How important is speed and responsiveness in the application?
24.	What would make the interface easy to learn and use?
25.	How much training should a new user need before using the system?
26.	Are there any school privacy or data policies the system must follow?
27.	What student information should be visible in the application?
28.	What student information should be hidden or protected?
29.	What would a successful solution look like to you?
30.	Is there anything else you would want included in the system that we have not discussed?
